text:
anyone seen someone do media queries written this way?

```@media(max-width: 767px)
{
  body.homepage .sc-header-banner .subhead{
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }
}```

Just wondering if people are teaching to write css this way. Got a new hire that keeps doing it. obviously functionally it works, but not sure if It just looks wrong to me because I’ve been doing this a long time and I’m not hip to a new thing, or what?

specifically referring to the brackets.

I would write it like this:
```@media(max-width: 767px){
  body.homepage .sc-header-banner .subhead{
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }
}```
